data.title: Privilege Ibiza Season Round Up, party calendar Privilege 2019
data.meta_description: Party calendar Privilege Ibiza 2019. Take a look at the exciting breakdown of events at Privilege this summer. Clubbing news and reviews, official tickets Ibiza
data.text:
Take a look at the exciting breakdown of events at Privilege this summer. Party calendar

Not only the biggest club on Ibiza, but the biggest club in the world has now announced the season line-up for 2019.

The impressive day-to-day line ups at Privilege keep getting stronger and stronger every year, with 2019 holding a diverse selection of events six days a week. Each evening will present a different genre of music; A factor that makes this superclub stand out from the rest, as Privilege can guarantee that there will be something to please everybody’s eardrums at least one night a week.

With the season just beginning, we bring you all the events Privilege has to offer in one article.

Read on to find out which date is the perfect party for you.

MONDAY'S WITH ONE THIRD

Start your week as a means to go on, and that is with some serious energy, good vibes and quality music, provided to you by the heavyweight Asian promoters, Maddog and One Third.

After regular collaborations with Privilege in previous years, 2019 will see both powerful brands join forces to host a magical residency that will run from Monday 1 July until 2 October.

Some of the biggest names in the Spanish electronic music industry will be on hand to provide the ultimate feel-good groove, house and bass rhythm. Listen here for a taste.

For more information and tickets click here.

JOIN THE RESISTANCE ON TUESDAY'S

It's no doubt that Tuesday’s at Privilege is the place to be. The ULTRA label RESISTANCE return to its home at the biggest club in the world for nine unmissable dates. It all starts on 23 July and will finish on 17 September.

The powerhouse residency is jam-packed with all of Ibiza’s favourite DJ’s and Resistance 2019 has unveiled an unbelievable summer roster.

Global Ambassadors Carl Cox and Adam Beyer are confirmed, as well as one of the most talked about additions to their line-up, Hot Since 82. Eats Everything, Charlotte De Witte, Maceo Plex, Richie Hawtin, Jamie Jones, Joris Voorn, Joseph Capriati, Kölsch, Loco Dice, Nic Fanciulli and more will also hit the decks.

WEDNESDAY'S WELCOME MANYCOME

Taking control of the Vista Club on Wednesday nights from 3 July until 18 September, Privilege welcomes Manycome, the techno establishment which gives some of the best female DJs of the moment centre stage.

International artists such as Marika Rossa, Lilly palmer, Elena Pavla, Amber and Nusha are among the names fired up to take us to a techno paradise.

For more info and tickets click here.

THE FAMOUS SUPERMARXTÉ ON FRIDAY'S

One of Ibiza’s most iconic parties, SuperMartXé will return to Friday nights at Privilege from 28 June until 27 September for fourteen fun-filled weeks, marking their 11th flamboyant season on the White Isle. This summer, SuperMartXé will return to their house roots, showcasing some of the most elegant classics of the genre to some of the greatest names in the industry.

Acts confirmed include 2manydjs, Benny Benassi, Mark Knight, Fedde Le Grand, WEISS, Illyus & Barrientos and many more.

For more info and tickets to the hottest party in Ibiza click here.

A REGGAETON RAVE SATURDAY'S AT BRUTAL IBIZA

Brutal Ibiza is the fiercest reggaeton party to debut in Ibiza, every sizzling Saturday from 8 June until 28 September.

Witness live, Latin and urban performances from the finest names in the business. A special date during the residency is Thursday 4 July, where Maluma will star in a very special show, and his only appearance in Ibiza.

Click here for tickets to Brutal and click here to for more about Maluma.

SOLID SUNDAY'S WITH SOLID GROOVES

Back with a vengeance, Solid Grooves returns to the Vista Club in Privilege for their second consecutive year, with a tongue in cheek statement, ‘Fcuk the Fakes'.

Running from 23rd June until 22nd September, Solid Grooves has a brand new concept designed to represent the more authentic, unpretentious side of the islands club culture, rebelling against the crowd who have become accustomed to the VIP experience the island has capitalised in recent years.

The bill includes a stand-out roster of tech-house heaven, including globally acclaimed DJs such as Cassy, Skream, Michael Bibi, Route 94, Darius Syrossian, Richy Ahead and more. Solid Grooves has also become a platform for the latest up-and-coming tech-talented newbies to take centre stage. Mason Collective, Mason Maynard, tINI, wAFF, Latmun Detlef and FUSE resident Seb Zito are included in the summer shenanigans.

See below for Michael Bibi's summer smash, 'Hanging Tree'.

Click here for full season line up and tickets.

There you have it. Six days of top-quality music of all genres. If you haven’t found yourself dancing until sunrise underneath the dazzling, panorama-view, glass windows in the famous Vista Club, then it is an absolute must and a vision all clubbers will remember forever.

Privilege Ibiza opened its doors on Saturday 2 June and will keep them wide open for all the shakers on the island until 28 September.

See you on the dancefloor!

Words: Holly Woulfe
